cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel multi-class MKL framework for discriminative feature selection and representation learning. The paper focuses on classification tasks and uses multiple kernels to obtain an efficient representation in the feature space. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning)
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition)
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence)
- cs.CL (Computation and Language)
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing)
